channel.description:
Do you believe they exist?

personally i dont think any exist at this time in the rest of our galaxy, but they could have existed wether in or out of our galaxy.

item.title: Aliens
item.dc:creator: @billygotshot billygotshot
item.description:
@billygotshot wrote:

lol after reading the post above somehow I thought of something. Well what if we were a superior “alien” race on mars. Then we used up most of the resources there so we started going to earth. We polluted the hell out of Mars and ended up destroying the ozone causing all life to die. Then when we moved to earth somehow we destroyed everything or only a few select people survived and those happened to be cavemen? That would be really weird.

item.dc:creator: @Lanthus20 Lanthus20
item.description:
@Lanthus20 wrote:

[quote=“ThatOneServer, post:1, topic:188608”]Do you believe they exist?

Also, couldn’t Mars harbor life?

personally i dont think any exist at this time in the rest of our galaxy, but they could have existed wether in or out of our galaxy.[/quote]

the definition of alien is basically, “foreigner” so you’d have to be more specific, but yes I get what you are talking about. I think it possible. We have discovered planets that MIGHT be capable of supporting life, so why not? mars being the closest example. there is evidence of past water. Which is the basis of all life. So if you have the materials why wouldn’t there be? Perhaps there are aliens, perhaps not. Nobody can say for sure wether or not there is aliens but I think yes.

They were perfectionists, they did everything perfectly, following what God told them… Also, to counter-argument his theory, how in the world did those Aliens show up back then and then not come back for tens of thousands of years. Also, Why in the world would they build something so perfect, for no good reason?

The distance between our planet and theres could maybe be so far that it takes thousands of years to get back. And you never know, maybe they had some hidden purpose.

“Religion has actually convinced people that there’s an invisible man, living in the sky, who watches everything you do every minute of every day. And the invisible man has a special list of 10 things he does not want you to do. And if you do any of these 10 things, he has a special place full of fire and smoke and burning and torture and anguish where he will send you to live and suffer and burn and choke and scream and cry forever and ever til the end of time…but he loves you.” – George Carlin

Is that easier to believe than aliens?
